<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[986,1133,1023,1047]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" genus="Eira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis box="[986,1133,1023,1047]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="213">Eira barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium-sized mustelid
</emphasis>
with a long body and neck, short, dorsoventrally flattened, head and short, round ears. Its pelage is dark brown with the head lighter than the dorsum and a whitish spot on the throat. The tail is long, dark and has long hairs.
</paragraph>
